# This is the mirror's root .gitignore, maintained as a STATIC file.
#
# It is renamed to repo-root `.gitignore` on the mirror by the
# path-rename directive in `paths.allowlist`
# (`.github/public-mirror/gitignore.mirror==>.gitignore`), so it ships
# inside filter-repo's own commit rather than as a synthesized commit
# stacked on top of filter-repo's output. Stacking a synth commit on
# top of filter-repo's output is exactly what made every source-change
# run diverge from the previous mirror tip and force-push, breaking
# consumers' `git pull` (issue #208). Shipping it through filter-repo
# keeps the mirror fast-forwarding on routine runs.
#
# This file MUST be kept in sync BY HAND with what `paths.allowlist`
# ships. When you add or remove a shipped path in `paths.allowlist`,
# add or remove the matching `!/<path>` un-ignore line here. It is NOT
# regenerated from `paths.allowlist` at runtime — runtime generation is
# what required a post-filter synth step in the first place; a static
# file removes that need entirely. (A future CI drift-check that
# *asserts* this file matches the allowlist would be fine, but it must
# be a check, not a commit-producing step.)
#
# The mirror needs its OWN .gitignore (not the source repo's root
# .gitignore): the source's .gitignore un-ignores paths that exist in
# the private repo but are deliberately EXCLUDED from the mirror by
# `paths.allowlist` (memory/, output-styles/, plans/, designs/, the
# nested .claude/, .github/). Shipping the source .gitignore would make
# a consumer's `git status` reference un-ignore rules for paths that do
# not exist in their clone. This file un-ignores exactly the mirror's
# shipped set and nothing else.

# Ignore everything by default, then un-ignore shipped files.
/*

# The .gitignore itself must not be ignored.
!/.gitignore

# Shipped paths (keep in sync with paths.allowlist):
!/README.md
!/LICENSE
!/PATENTS
!/PRIOR_ART.md
!/CODEOWNERS
!/CONTRIBUTORS
!/.global-claude-config/
!/.global-claude-config/**
!/CLAUDE.md
!/agents/
!/agents/**
!/skills/
!/skills/**
!/rules/
!/rules/**
!/hooks/
!/hooks/**
!/keybindings.json
!/settings.json
